Playing impressions Omega VII Euro â a fun, soft and lightweight looping rubber with an enormous catapult: Even before hitting the first rally, I noticed how feather light the rubber is.
FH drives close to the table are crisp, very fast, yet controlled.
The prominent catapult renders FH drives from mid-distance near effortless, and it was a lot of fun to slam away 1-2 meters behind the table.
FH loops executed with compact medium-fast arm movements is where this rubber truly shines, producing a loud clicking sound and very dynamic feeling.
It is easy to execute FH loops with excellent control, depth, and a medium-high throw angle, which provides ample clearance over the net.
BH looping with this rubber feels great.
Aggressive service returns, on the other hand, are quite easy to execute with the Omega VII Euro, aided the grippy topsheet and lack of sensitivity for incoming spin.
Finally, the very low weight of the O7E will appeal to skilled kids and other players who prefer light equipment.
Opening FH loops against heavy backspin are easy to execute as the top-sheet firmly grips the plastic ball.
